Senator Ahmed Lawan has been sworn in as the President of the ninth Senate by the Clerk of the National Assembly, Mohammed Sani-Omolori. This followed Lawan’s defeat of Senator Ali Ndume by 79 votes to 28 in an election that saw 107 senators vote. Sani-Omolori administered the Oaths of Allegiance and Office to Lawan before […] Ahmed Lawan sworn-in as Senate President Source: Daily Post